HEADWORD: Son-in-law
<hw>Son"-in-law`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sons-in-law</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The husband of one's
daughter; a man in his relationship to his wife's parents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To take me as for thy <qex>son in lawe</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sonless</ent>⟦br⟧
